Languages in general fascinate me, and I will always be on a mission to learn them and respect them. And I think there are beauties that in no way resemble each other but are equally as magnificent.

Those may seem insane reasons to find it beautiful, but I enjoy playing with the language & discovering new ways to articulate myself. There is room for differences in opinion and perception, but must we completely bash one thing in order to validate another? I don’t think we do.

For me, English is beautiful because of its inconsistencies. Aware that sounds insane, but the syntax is flexible. Words are malleable. There’s almost a beautiful frustration and a tension within it. An identity crisis if you will where it’s always trying to figure out who it is.

While I do see the truth of many monolingual English speakers being high & mighty about English, I do want to say that you don’t have to diminish one thing in order to lift another up. There is beauty in so many things, and those beauties can exist independently of each other.
